<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Words Containing TH — The Most Common English Digraph</h1>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">TH is the most frequent digraph in English — it appears in THE, THAT, THIS, THERE, and THEM. In Scrabble, T(1) + H(4) gives a 5-point base, but the real power is volume: hundreds of common words contain TH, meaning you'll almost always have a play available when holding these two tiles together.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">TH at a Glance</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
  <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">T(1) + H(4) base</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">800+</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Valid TH words</p></div>
    <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">#1</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Most common digraph</p></div>
  </div>
</div>

<p>With 6 T tiles and 2 H tiles in the bag, drawing T+H together is more common than you'd think. Having a deep TH vocabulary means you're never stuck — there's always a play somewhere on the board.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Top Scoring TH Words</h2>

<div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
    <thead class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800">
      <tr>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Word</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Points</th>
        <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Length</th>
