<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy for TH Words</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">-TH endings are hard to hook:</span> WARMTH, GROWTH, FILTH — opponents can't easily add letters after TH. Use them to shut down board sections defensively.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">TH- starters open the board:</span> THROW, THRIVE, THRASH place tiles outward from the centre, reaching premium squares at the edges. Great for opening moves.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">THE/THAT/THIS build parallels:</span> Common words make excellent parallel plays — lay THE alongside an existing word to form multiple 2-letter crossings.</p>
